  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhanced Media-CSOPartnerships for Inclusive Local Governance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	Organise 1-day non-residential project governance meeting and including national project launch involving 30 GJA National Executive Council members.
2.	Organise 1-day 3-zonal non-residential project inception meetingsfor 70selected journalistsand 30grant partners.
3.	Publish project profiles, case studies and key results of STAR-Ghana grant partners(i.e. pull-outs in Graphic).
4.	Establish and organiselocal governance TV-radioprogrammes for policy advocacy and accountability by journalists and STAR-Ghana CSOs partners.
5.	Produce Evidence-based audio-visual clips on project results and disseminate through media platforms. 
6.	Organize Quarterly community forum for partners, citizens, GESI, media and duty bearers on inclusive local governance and key policy issues.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive media platforms established for advocacy and accountability on local governance issues by journalists and STAR-Ghana Grant partners, and b) Citizens mobilised around local level elections through media platforms for inclusive development at local and national levels policy choices.</narrative>
  </description>
